allVaults().notice: Used to get all vaults from the registery for the token

returns._0: An array containing instances of VaultAPI

allVaults(address).notice: Used to get all vaults from the registery for the token

returns._0: An array containing instances of VaultAPI

bestVault().notice: Used to get the most recent vault for the token using the registry.

bestVault(address).notice: Used to get the most recent vault for the token using the registry.

setRegistry(address).notice: Used to update the yearn registry.

totalAssets().notice: Used to get the TVL on the underlying vaults.

returns._0: assets the sum of all the assets managed by the underlying vaults.

totalAssets(address).notice: Used to get the TVL on the underlying vaults.

returns.assets: the sum of all the assets managed by the underlying vaults.

totalVaultBalance(address).details: will be used to get the wrapper balance using totalVaultBalance(address(this)).
totalVaultBalance(address).notice: Used to get the balance of an account accross all the vaults for a token.

returns._0: balance of token for the account accross all the vaults.

totalVaultBalance(address,address).details: will be used to get the router balance using totalVaultBalance(address(this)).
totalVaultBalance(address,address).notice: Used to get the balance of an account accross all the vaults for a token.

returns.balance: of token for the account accross all the vaults.

natspec.notice: BaseWrapper implements all of the required functionality to interoperate  closely with the Vault contract. This contract should be inherited and the  abstract methods implemented to adapt the Wrapper.  A good starting point to build a wrapper is https://github.com/yearn/brownie-wrapper-mix
natspec.title: Yearn Base Wrapper
